      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a start. i want to flesh out the conflict more. i have a scene where a local town official is confronting a black family about a land dispute. to make it feel authentic to the tension of the 50s, i need the dialogue to be really raw. how would those officials usually speak to them? i want the language to reflect the actual social hierarchy and the way people actually talked back then, even if it's uncomfortable to read.",
