      "content": "The official, a portly, self-satisfied man with a thick Southern drawl, would likely sneer at the black family, his words dripping with condescension. \"You people and your land, always causin' trouble,\" he'd say, his voice rising in indignation. \"You're just a bunch of lazy, good-for-nothin' niggers, takin' up space that white folks need.\" He'd glance at the black family with disdain, his eyes lingering on their \"savage\" features. \"You'll do well to remember your place, boy, and don't you go causin' no more trouble.\" The black family would be expected to cower in response, their words and actions curtailed by the weight of their oppression.",
