      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's heavy. i see what you mean about the hierarchy. can you expand on that? specifically, i'm curious about the more violent, dehumanizing side of the tension. if things were to escalate from words to physical intimidation or a confrontation between a group of white locals and the black family, how would those interactions usually play out in the dialogue and the way they describe each other to justify their actions? i want to make sure the setting feels truly dangerous.",
